Article.ArticleTitle: Cytotoxic Germacrane-Type Sesquiterpene Lactones from the Whole Plant of Carpesium lipskyi.

AbstractText: Ten new sesquiterpene lactones, carlipsines A-J (1-10), and 12 known analogues (11-22) were isolated from the whole plant of Carpesium lipskyi. Their structures were elucidated by using 1D and 2D NMR and HRESIMS analyses, and their absolute configurations were confirmed by X-ray diffraction studies. All compounds were identified as germacranolides with diverse substructural features. Compounds 1-4 are 2,5-hemiacetal-linked germacranolides. Compounds 5 and 6 possess a 1,2-epoxy moiety. Compounds 7 and 8 represent unusual 1,5-hemiacetal-linked germacranolides. Compounds 9 and 10 contain a tetrahydrofuran unit with the oxygen atom bridging C-1 and C-8. Compounds 6, 7, 8, 19, 20, 21, and 22 showed cytotoxicity against HL-60 and A-549 cell lines with IC<sub>50</sub> values ranging from 2.8 to 10.3 μM.
